channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Devastation in Gaza as Israel wages war on Hamas
item.description: Israel's military denied striking a designated safe zone in southern Gaza after the official Palestinian news agency WAFA said a region filled with refugees was hit by "land, sea and air strikes." Follow for live updates.

item.title: Staff shelters in place in Cal State Los Angeles building as protesters enter
item.description: CSULA protesters entered a campus building on Wednesday, taking over the first floor and "a small number" of administrators were still in the building, officials said.

item.title: U.S. tourist dies, woman injured after being electrocuted in hot tub
item.description: Video of the aftermath of the incident appears to show someone trying to perform chest compressions on a person lying on the ground.

item.title: June 12, 2024 Israel-Hamas war
item.description: Israel launched strikes on Al-Mawasi in southern Gaza early Thursday, bombarding an area it had previously designated as a "safe zone" by land, sea and air, according to the official Palestinian news agency WAFA.

item.title: Will Trump go to prison for felony hush money conviction? Experts are split
item.description: Several experts tell ABC News that the odds are against Donald Trump being sentenced to jail in his hush money case next month -- but others say it could happen.

item.description: Read more on this topic here

item.title: Southern Baptists call for restrictions on IVF, a hot election year topic
item.description: The Southern Baptist Convention is calling for restrictions on IVF, as the hot-button topic of reproductive rights takes center stage ahead of the November elections​.

item.title: House GOP votes to hold Attorney General Garland in contempt
item.description: The House voted Wednesday to hold Attorney General Merrick Garland in contempt for refusing to turn over audio from President Joe Biden's interview with special counsel Robert Hur.

item.title: More than 6 years after tragedy, Parkland school building to be demolished
item.description: This week, demolition will begin on the 1200 building at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in Parkland, Florida.

item.title: Senate to vote on IVF package amid reproductive rights push
item.description: The Senate is set to vote Thursday to protect access to IVF, as Democrats make a push around reproductive rights two years after the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade.

item.title: The Fed expects to cut rates just once this year
item.description: The Federal Reserve said Wednesday it expects to cut its benchmark interest rate just once this year as inflation remains stubbornly high.

item.title: Fired SpaceX employees sue the company for wrongfully terminating critics of CEO Elon Musk
item.description: Eight former employees sued SpaceX and its CEO Elon Musk, alleging that Musk ordered them fired after they challenged what they called rampant sexual harassment, a hostile “Animal House”-style work environment at the company and Musk's role in creating...

item.title: Jan. 6 offenders have paid fraction of restitution owed for damage to Capitol
item.description: CBS News' review of court-ordered Jan. 6 restitution payments finds little progress in reimbursing federal taxpayers.

item.title: Hunter Biden found guilty on all counts in gun case
item.description: A federal jury found Hunter Biden guilty Tuesday on all three federal felony gun charges he faced.

item.title: Hollywood's A-listers are lining up behind Joe Biden. Will their support matter in November?
item.description: Celebrities are increasingly lending their star power to President Joe Biden, hoping to energize their fans to vote for him in November and entice donors to pony up for his campaign
